rows.agenda:
Briefing by the Department of Budget and Management (DBM) on the following:

a) Total budget allotted by the government for the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) since 2016, and the actual disbursement; 
b) Breakdown of budget allotment and actual disbursement by SDG; 
c) Guidelines followed in approving Program Convergence Budgeting (PCB)-SDG proposals endorsed by the Department of Economy, Planning and Development (DEPDev)/Subcommittee on the SDGs (SCSDGs) for funding under RA 11467 (amending the National Internal Revenue Code of 1997, as amended); 
d) Clarification on whether revenues generated under RA 11467 are accounted for separately from the budget of national government agencies under the General Appropriations Act; 
e) Guidelines followed in creating a special trust fund for the Universal Health Care (UHC) under RA 11467; 
f) Treatment of unused funds generated under RA 11467, specifically for UHC, for the SDGs, and for the upgrading of health equipment; and
g) Reasons for the disapproval of the eight programs, activities, and projects for FY 2025 PCB on the SDGs

Organizational meeting – Approval of the Committee Rules of Procedure

Briefing by the Department of Education (DepEd) on the following:
a) Mandate and legal basis;
b) Plans, programs, deliverables, and other relevant statistical data for School Year 2025 – 2026;
c) Report of accomplishments and challenges; and
d) Legislative agenda/priorities for the 20th Congress

• Briefing/update by the Department of Education (DepEd) on matters relating to the strengthened Senior High School (SHS) Program:
a) Targeted pilot implementation of the strengthened SHS Program for School Year 2025 – 2026 and onwards;
b) Adjusted technical professional track's elective subjects for SHS, in relation to the grant of upgraded National Certification levels to SHS graduates; 
c) Proposed downloading of higher education’s General Curriculum subjects to the SHS Curriculum;
d) Proposed removal by the Commission on Higher Education of the Higher Education Institutions’ Bridging Program; and 
e) Other relevant information

• Briefing by the Philippine Guarantee Corporation, Land Bank of the Philippines, and Development Bank of the Philippines on the status of implementation of RA 11494, otherwise known as the Bayanihan to Recover as One Act, specifically on Section 4 (COVID-19 Response and Recovery Interventions) and Section 10 (Appropriations and Standby Fund)

• Update by the DepEd on the following:
a) Implementation of the Balik-Eskwela Program for the opening of classes for School Year 2025-2026;
b) Data on learner’s enrollment, school infrastructure, and learning materials, and other relevant data/information; and
c) Other related concerns

Briefing by the Department of Education (DepEd) on the following:

a) Planned implementation of the Strengthened Senior High School (SHS) Program for School Year 2025 – 2026;
b) Adjusted technical professional track's elective subjects for SHS; 
c) Comments of the Commission on Higher Education and Technical Educational and Skills Development Authority on the Strengthened SHS Program; and
d) Other relevant information
